 progress without endangering the environment and ourselves.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aClimatic changesxCalifornia. 0aClimatic changesxEconomic aspectsxCalifornia. 0aClimatic changesxEconomic aspectszCalifornia. 0aClimatic changesxEnvironmental aspectsxCaliforniaxCalifornia. 0aClimatic changesxEnvironmental aspectszCalifornia. 0aClimatic changeszCalifornia. 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Meteorology & Climatology.2bisacsh  acalifornia beauty.  acarbon emissions.  aclimate change in california.  aclimate change risk.  aclimate change.  aclimatology.  adiscussion books.  aearth sciences.  aeasy to read.  aecology.  aeducational books.  aengaging.  aenvironment and the economy.  aenvironment issues.  afixing climate change.  aglobal heating.  aglobal warming.  agoing green.  ainformative books.  alearning from experts.  alower carbon.  ameteorology.  apolitics and climate.  aprotecting the earth.  apublic health.  athinking about the future.  aunited states climate.1 aRoland-Holst, David, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095380240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520953802423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520953802/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles